The paper deals with algorithms for testing isomorphism of graphs, which falls under the category of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM). The specific type of graphs being studied are circular-arc graphs, which are a subclass of intersection graphs, and thus the paper may also be relevant to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) and Data Structures (cs.DS). The use of decomposition trees and canonical representations suggests a connection to Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Combinatorics (cs.CC).
